  <title>AFL Tribunal: Hawks veteran Luke Hodge guilty of striking</title>
  <content>
Hawthorn veteran Luke Hodge will miss Sunday's clash against Richmond after the AFL tribunal upheld his one-match ban for striking.
Hodge was charged with striking Sydney's Tom Papley during the second quarter of the Hawks' six-point win over the Swans at the MCG on Friday night.Photo: AAP
The jury - consisting of Paul Williams, Stewart Loewe and Richard Loveridge - took just over 20 minutes to find the four-time premiership star guilty.
AAP, more to come
